    "name": "Mesh convergence study — non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw FEA model",
    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model using three successive mesh densities (coarse: ~85 000 elements, medium: ~210 000 elements, fine: ~520 000 elements). The Richardson extrapolation procedure was applied to the predicted construct stiffness and yield force QoIs. The grid convergence index (GCI) was computed for each QoI pair; all GCI values fell below 2.1%, confirming that the medium mesh density achieves discretization-error levels consistent with Gradation 3 requirements. The study was executed in Ansys Mechanical 2023 R1 on the FDA high-performance computing cluster.",
